    "encrypted": "false",
    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "### Random Block\r\nYou can add entire sequences inside a `play random` block. In this example, every time the loop repeats, it will choose a new style of song to play (Electro, Pop, or Hip-Hop).\r\n\r\nAdd a fourth sequence to this code to play a Heavy Rock set of beats, bass, and lead. This requires:\r\n\r\n1) Adding a new `play together` block inside the `play random` block [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=flyout-id:play_together_toolbox---id:play_random_workspace)\r\n2) Adding 3 new `play` blocks and choosing 3 new tracks from the Heavy Metal pack\r\n\r\nPress the <code style=\"background-color: #fca401; color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px1 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">Run</code> button! You should hear a different selection of beat, bass, and lead tracks as the song plays!",
    "offer_browser_tts": "true",
    "use_secondary_finish_button": "false",
    "hide_share_and_remix": "true",
